				<td colspan="2"><span>Suggestions:1
<br />

<br />
Ctrl+alt+del close EVERYTHING you can.  2(warning you must restart and xp will reinstall everything) if you are running WinXp the factory default is something REALLY lame and its ACPI computer (you can check this by right clickign on the &quot;my computer&quot;  computer icon and clicking properties.
<br />
Then click the hardware tab, then 'device manager&quot; button. 
<br />

<br />
Now in here you should see something labeled &quot;computer&quot; with + sigh click the + sign.  If underneath says ACPI, you need to right click on it and then properties.  Click the &quot;driver&quot; tab and then Update driver.  Chose install from a list and click next.  Chose &quot;dont search I will chose the driver to install&quot; and go next.    Look for &quot;standard PC&quot;. Chose that and click next.
<br />

<br />
Now you are prolly asking wtf this is a pain in the a$, why am I donig this?   Simple, the retards at M$ decided ACPI (or whever its called) would be the default.  So now you ask, why is this a problem?  Well advanced users realize that ACPI has set EVERY peice of hardware to the same d*mn IRQ.  IRQ=Interupt Request (or something like that I dont care what all the acronyms stand for anymore)  What IRQ is , is basically which device has priority over the others.  
<br />

<br />
Come on Ergo wtf get to the point.  Anyway by APCI setting all devices to the same IRQ, NOTHING has priority and this causes about a 1 second lag when say oh your Soundcard is playing music, network card is connected to the internet (or dialup modem) and your Video card is trying to render 3d images.  See the problem now?  Anyway  give this a shot if nothing else works, I play in windowed mode highest reso my card will go and I have 0 lag unless im boxing 2 chars at once on this comp.  
<br />

<br />
Help this helps.
<br />

<br />
P.S. I hate windoze~
<br />
</span></td>
